Aim: Write a PL\SQL functions
•	To find the largest number amongst given two numbers.
•	To find the total number of employees from emp relation given the employee number.
•	To return the email id of the employee consisting of firstname and lastname.


Solution:
1. To Find the Largest Number Between Two Numbers

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION largest_of_two(x IN INT, y IN INT) RETURN INT AS
BEGIN
    IF x > y THEN
        RETURN x;
    ELSE
        RETURN y;
    END IF;
END;
/

Calling Function Directly in SQLPlus:
SELECT largest_of_two(15, 10) FROM dual;

2. To Find the Total Number of Employees

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION number_of_employees RETURN NUMBER AS
    total NUMBER := 0;
BEGIN
    SELECT COUNT(*) INTO total FROM emp;
    RETURN total;
END;
/

3. To Return the Email ID of the Employee

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION email_return(v_fname mytable.fname%TYPE, v_lname mytable.lname%TYPE) RETURN VARCHAR2 AS
BEGIN
    RETURN v_fname || '.' || v_lname || '@sitnagpur.siu.edu.in';
END;
/
Outcome: These functions collectively teach students how to perform various operations using PL/SQL functions, such as comparisons, aggregate queries, and string manipulations.



